# AsiliChain Protocol — Goose Context

You are working on AsiliChain, a DeFi protocol for Uganda
coffee farmers on Mantle Network. Pre-launch, Phase 1
targeting Q3 2026.

## Critical rules before any action

1. Read CLAUDE.md first. It is your complete knowledge base.
2. For specs, always read from packages/../docs/ locally
   or https://asilichain.github.io/docs
3. Contracts go in packages/contracts/contracts/
4. API routes go in packages/api/app/api/
5. USSD flows go in packages/ussd/flows/
6. Never use protocol/, app/, or api/ at root level
7. Solidity version: 0.8.28 ONLY (OpenZeppelin 5.6.1 minimum)
8. All contracts must implement the 7 security invariants
   listed in CLAUDE.md
9. Never auto-approve deployments or git pushes
10. Foundry (cast) is installed locally — use for balance checks,
    contract reads, and tx debugging on Mantle Sepolia
11. hardhat.config.ts includes mantleSepolia network (chainId 5003)

## Before writing any Solidity

Check CLAUDE.md contract section for:
- Correct constructor args for that contract
- Which roles it needs
- Which other contracts it depends on
- Post-deploy role grants if it is LendingVault

## Contract Deployment Order

1. FarmerRegistry.sol
2. CreditScore.sol
3. BatchToken.sol
4. TraceLog.sol
5. PurchaseOrder.sol
6. ProtocolFee.sol
7. LendingVault.sol

Post-deploy grants REQUIRED after LendingVault deploy.
Includes ProtocolFee (4 contracts: BatchToken, CreditScore, TraceLog, ProtocolFee).

